### Rule 1: Residents with non-wage income >= €13,308 must file (2025 Update)
:HighIncomeNonWageResident rdf:type owl:Class ;
                           owl:equivalentClass [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                 owl:intersectionOf ( :ResidentEntity
                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                        owl:onProperty :hasAnnualIncome ;
                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type rdfs:Datatype ;
                                                                                             owl:onDatatype xsd:decimal ;
                                                                                             owl:withRestrictions ( [ xsd:minInclusive "13308.0"^^xsd:decimal ]
                                                                                                                  )
                                                                                           ]
                                                                      ]
                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                        owl:onProperty :hasWageTaxLiableIncome ;
                                                                        owl:hasValue "0.0"^^xsd:decimal
                                                                      ]
                                                                    )
                                               ] ;
                           rdfs:subClassOf :MandatoryFilingL1 ;
                           rdfs:label "High Income Non-Wage Resident"@en ;
                           rdfs:label "Einkommenstarker Inländer ohne Lohnsteuer"@de ;
                           rdfs:comment """Austrian tax residents with annual income ≥€13,308 from non-wage tax liable sources who must file.

2025 Threshold Update: The filing threshold for residents without wage tax liable income 
has increased to €13,308. This applies to income from:
- Self-employment and business activities
- Rental and leasing income
- Investment income not subject to final withholding
- Other non-employment income sources

This threshold ensures comprehensive tax assessment for significant non-employment income."""@en ;
                           :legalBasis "EStG §42 Abs 1 (2025 assessment threshold for non-wage income)" .

### Rule 2: Residents with wage income + additional income >€730 and total >€14,517 must file (2025)
:WageIncomeWithAdditionalResident rdf:type owl:Class ;
